{
  "schemaVersion": "2.0.0",
  "bookId": "beginner-board-rules",
  "chapterId": "01-board-coordinates",
  "title": "Board Coordinates And The First Map",
  "subtitle": "Before pieces make sense, the board must become a map.",
  "eloRange": "0-300",
  "requiredTier": "free",
  "estimatedMinutes": 18,
  "learningObjectives": [
    "Recognize the correct board orientation.",
    "Name files, ranks, and coordinates.",
    "Read a move as from-square to to-square.",
    "Play 1.e4 from the starting position."
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "id": "map-before-moves",
      "title": "The Board Is A Map",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "id": "b01-c01-p01",
          "type": "prose",
          "body_md": "A chessboard is not only 64 squares. It is a map. Strong players do not say \"move this pawn up two.\" They say **e2 to e4** because the square names let everyone see the same position in their mind.\n\nIn this chapter, you will learn the board language that every later lesson will use."
        },
        {
          "id": "b01-c01-d01",
          "type": "board_diagram",
          "title": "The empty board",
          "fen": "8/8/8/8/8/8/8/8 w - - 0 1",
          "orientation": "white",
          "highlights": [
            {
              "square": "h1",
              "colorRole": "best"
            },
            {
              "square": "a8",
              "colorRole": "safe"
            }
          ],
          "caption_md": "Correct setup starts with a light square on White's bottom-right corner: h1.",
          "assertions": [
            {
              "type": "highlight_exists",
              "square": "h1"
            }
          ],
          "exports": {
            "png": "assets/diagrams/b01-c01-d01-empty-board.png",
            "hash": "8e15916fb28f316a7d4626a173e86dd691102f2d3f10f5e703a93a68c13acc26"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "b01-c01-d02",
          "type": "board_diagram",
          "title": "The four center squares",
          "fen": "8/8/8/8/8/8/8/8 w - - 0 1",
          "orientation": "white",
          "highlights": [
            {
              "square": "d4",
              "colorRole": "target"
            },
            {
              "square": "e4",
              "colorRole": "target"
            },
            {
              "square": "d5",
              "colorRole": "target"
            },
            {
              "square": "e5",
              "colorRole": "target"
            }
          ],
          "caption_md": "The center squares d4, e4, d5, and e5 are marked because later your pieces will fight for them.",
          "assertions": [
            {
              "type": "highlight_exists",
              "square": "d4"
            },
            {
              "type": "highlight_exists",
              "square": "e4"
            },
            {
